{"ticker": "PRME", "company": "Prime Medicine", "weight_sum": 3.73, "etfs": ["ARKVX", "ARKG", "ARKUX", "ARKSX"], "is_private": false, "query": "($PRME OR \"Prime Medicine\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since_time:1777634260 until_time:1777641460", "n_fetched": 1, "n_kept": 1, "n_dropped": 0, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2049863058529362354", "url": "https://x.com/TheFoxRadar/status/2049863058529362354", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/TheFoxRadar/status/2049863058529362354", "text": "$PRME \n\nDe novo proteins: the leap that could unlock in vivo delivery of gene editing\n\nThe biggest bottleneck of prime editing therapies has always been in vivo delivery. The full prime editor construct is large (~6\u20137 kb), which exceeds the capacity of a single AAV (limit ~4.7 kb) and forces the use of dual systems with loss of efficiency, or LNPs that work well in the liver but have limitations in other tissues and generate immunogenicity upon repeated dosing.\n\nFor two decades we have lived through two major waves of delivery:\n\n\u2022 AAVs (2000s\u20132010s) enabled the first approved in vivo gene therapies (Luxturna, Zolgensma).\n\n\u2022 LNPs (used in COVID vaccines and mRNA therapies) solved large-scale RNA delivery.\n\nNow we are entering a third wave thanks to de novo protein design (proteins created from scratch using artificial intelligence): cages, lattices, and delivery handles can be fully programmable, encapsulating the prime editor + pegRNA as needed, targeting specific tissues, escaping the endosome with precision, and minimizing the immune response.\n\nIn short: we move from \u201chow do we deliver this?\u201d to \u201clet\u2019s design exactly the vehicle we need.\n\nThis advance is not incremental; it is enabling. It accelerates the shift from ex vivo to in vivo therapies, dramatically expands treatable indications, and reduces safety and manufacturing risks.\n\nIt is still in the preclinical phase. But the direction is clear, and the potential impact, transformative.\n\nThe field of gene editing is entering an exciting phase.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 5, "replyCount": 2, "likeCount": 32, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 3741, "createdAt": "Thu Apr 30 14:46:52 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 10, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049863058529362354", "displayTextRange": [0, 277], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "TheFoxRadar", "url": "https://x.com/TheFoxRadar", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/TheFoxRadar", "id": "2016491161033064448", "name": "The Fox Radar", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2018818076867784704/SUo4OLsD_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/2016491161033064448/1770236335", "description": "", "location": "Spain", "followers": 260, "following": 295, "status": "", "canDm": false, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Wed Jan 28 12:39:03 +0000 2026", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 742, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 30, "statusesCount": 310, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2035376290979549413"], "profile_bio": {"description": "Early-stage picks for high long-term returns | Sharing my investments, macro insights & real opportunities   Not Financial Advice. $PRME $AUR $ASTS", "entities": {"description": {"symbols": [{"indices": [131, 136], "text": "PRME"}, {"indices": [137, 141], "text": "AUR"}, {"indices": [142, 147], "text": "ASTS"}]}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [0, 5], "text": "PRME"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "204970086411